Former IFP leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi has completed his self-isolation and made a full recovery from COVID-19. He tested positive earlier this month. The 92-year-old never developed any symptoms. Courtesy #DStv403 ULUNDI - Former IFP leader Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi says he thanks God for his full recovery from COVID-19. The soon-to-be 92-year-old had five tests done and tested positive on the sixth. He says his existing medical conditions and age caused some concern, but he left it all in God's hands. READ: Buthelezi tests positive for COVID-19 "I was surprised when I was told that I was positive. So the doctors immediately said I must isolate. "They were debating whether I should go to hospital, isolate in quarantine, or in my house. So they finally said I can quarantine in my house," Buthelezi said. He stated his life was normal throughout the period of isolation and experienced no symptoms. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.